HEADWORD: Spondaical
<hw>Spon*da"ic*al</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>spondaicus</ets>, <ets>spondiacus</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>sponda⟦ium⟧que</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a
spondee; consisting of spondees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing spondees in excess; marked by spondees;
<as>as, a <ex>spondaic</ex> hexameter, <it>i. e.</it>, one which has a
spondee instead of a dactyl in the fifth foot</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spondee</ent>⟦br⟧
